[
    {
        "content": "<p>What's the correct type to do this in? Something that both <code>WithTop _</code> and <code>WithBot _</code> coerce into, with the obvious inherited order?</p>",
        "id": 503813154,
        "sender_full_name": "Jakob von Raumer",
        "timestamp": 1741272454
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Typo? <span aria-label=\"grinning\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f600\" role=\"img\" title=\"grinning\">:grinning:</span></p>",
        "id": 503813563,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1741272551
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I would expect <code>[1, 2].maximum &gt; [1, 2].minimum</code> but <code>[].maximum &lt; [].minimum</code></p>",
        "id": 503813632,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1741272568
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ah no, no Typo. Was thinking of <code>[1, 2].maximum &lt; [3, 4].minimum</code>.</p>",
        "id": 503813732,
        "sender_full_name": "Jakob von Raumer",
        "timestamp": 1741272597
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Should we instead have <code>List.max? : List α → WithTop α</code> and <code>List.max : List α → α</code>?</p>",
        "id": 503814099,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1741272683
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"310045\">Eric Wieser</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/217875-Is-there-code-for-X.3F/topic/List.2Emaximum.20_.20.3C.20List.2Eminimum/near/503813632\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I would expect <code>[1, 2].maximum &gt; [1, 2].minimum</code> but <code>[].maximum &lt; [].minimum</code></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Exactly. Right now, I can write down the inequality but Lean interprets it as in <code>WithBot Nat</code> because it adapts the type of the RHS and <code>WithBot Nat === Option Nat == WithTop Nat</code>.</p>",
        "id": 503814177,
        "sender_full_name": "Jakob von Raumer",
        "timestamp": 1741272708
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>While the correct type would be the order isomorphic to <code>WithBot (WithTop Nat)</code> or <code>WithTop (WithBot Nat)</code>.</p>",
        "id": 503814571,
        "sender_full_name": "Jakob von Raumer",
        "timestamp": 1741272801
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">([</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">maximum</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">map</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">WithTop</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">some</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">WithBot</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">some</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">([</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">minimum</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>works</p>",
